    <!--
    You can grab it from Telegram itself:

    For a 1:1 chat: send any message to your bot, 
    then call https://api.telegram.org/bot<YOUR_BOT_TOKEN>/getUpdates in a browser/curl. 
    
    In the JSON response, look at result[...].message.chat.id — that’s the chat id to use.

    For a group/channel: add the bot, send a message in the group, then call getUpdates the same way. 

    The message.chat.id will be negative (e.g., -1001234567890) for supergroups/channels. 

    If the bot doesn’t see messages, disable “Group Privacy” in BotFather (/setprivacy → Disable), 
    then try again.

    Keep the bot token private; once you have the chat_id, set it in telegram_chat_id.
    -->

